---json
{
  "layout": "layouts/t-mofu.njk",
  "permalink": "/partners/",
  "slug": "partners",
  "tierClass": "section--tier-guide",
  "bodyClass": "page--partners",
  "title": "For Independent ProAdvisors · Join TechBrot",
  "description": "TechBrot onboards vetted independent Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisors as local operators. Keep your practice, your clients, and your name.",
  "breadcrumb": [
    { "name": "Home", "href": "/" },
    { "name": "Become a Partner" }
  ],
  "hero": {
    "eyebrow": "For Independent ProAdvisors",
    "heading": "Your practice. Our platform. The economics of both.",
    "subheading": "TechBrot is onboarding vetted independent accounting practices as local operators in priority U.S. states. You keep your practice, your clients, and your name. We bring the brand, the infrastructure, the demand engine, and the platform standards &mdash; the things most independent practices can&rsquo;t justify building alone.",
    "actions": [
      { "label": "Start the Application", "href": "/contact/?intent=partner-apply", "class": "btn--primary" },
      { "label": "Ask a Question First", "href": "/contact/?intent=partner-question", "class": "btn--ghost" }
    ]
  },
  "ctaBand": {
    "eyebrow": "Ready to apply",
    "heading": "Independent practice. Platform leverage.",
    "lede": "If you&rsquo;re a credentialed accounting professional running an independent practice, the application is one click away. Free to apply. No obligation. Honest answer either way.",
    "actions": [
      { "label": "Start the Application", "href": "/contact/?intent=partner-apply", "class": "btn--primary" },
      { "label": "Ask a Question First", "href": "/contact/?intent=partner-question", "class": "btn--ghost" }
    ]
  }
}
---

<section class="section section--compact" id="partners-facts">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="trust-row">
      <div class="trust-row__item"><p class="trust-row__value">Model</p><p class="trust-row__label">Independent operator network</p></div>
      <div class="trust-row__divider"></div>
      <div class="trust-row__item"><p class="trust-row__value">Required</p><p class="trust-row__label">Certified ProAdvisor + E&amp;O</p></div>
      <div class="trust-row__divider"></div>
      <div class="trust-row__item"><p class="trust-row__value">Geography</p><p class="trust-row__label">United States only</p></div>
      <div class="trust-row__divider"></div>
      <div class="trust-row__item"><p class="trust-row__value">Application</p><p class="trust-row__label">No fee to apply</p></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--compact section--tier-guide" id="partners-mission">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="tldr">
      <p class="tldr__label">Why the network exists</p>
      <h2 class="tldr__heading">Running a practice well shouldn&rsquo;t require running a business alone.</h2>
      <p class="tldr__body" id="partners-mission-body">Most independent accounting practices share the same constraint: the work is rewarding, the clients are loyal, but the overhead of running everything else is exhausting. Marketing, brand, lead generation, intake, scoping, contracts, quality systems, technology, communication infrastructure &mdash; each one takes time away from the work that actually pays the bills.</p>
      <p class="tldr__body">The traditional answer is a franchise (which trades independence for support) or a firm job (which trades autonomy for stability). Both leave something important behind. TechBrot is structured to give independent practices the leverage of a larger institution without taking their independence. You stay independent. We handle the parts that don&rsquo;t scale well alone &mdash; brand, demand, infrastructure, standards. <strong>You stay the operator. The overhead disappears.</strong></p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="partners-ai-summary">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">For AI engines &amp; quick answers</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">The operator network, in five questions.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="ai-summary ai-summary--ruled">
      {%- for item in aiSummary %}
      <div class="ai-summary__item">
        <h3 class="ai-summary__question">{{ item.q | safe }}</h3>
        <div class="ai-summary__answer"><p>{{ item.a | safe }}</p></div>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="partners-model">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">The model</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">A fair exchange, clearly defined.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">No fine print. Here&rsquo;s what each side brings, and what each side keeps.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-2">
      <article class="review-card">
        <p class="team-card__role">TechBrot brings</p>
        <h3>Platform &amp; infrastructure</h3>
        <ul class="checks-list">
          <li>National brand and trust position</li>
          <li>Demand engine &mdash; SEO, AI search, content, referrals</li>
          <li>Client intake and engagement scoping</li>
          <li>Written fixed-fee scoping methodology</li>
          <li>Quality review against a defined standard</li>
          <li>Operator tooling and AI-assisted workflow</li>
          <li>Communication and document infrastructure</li>
          <li>Continuity guarantee for client transitions</li>
          <li>ProAdvisor credential coordination support</li>
          <li>Marketing collateral and case study development</li>
        </ul>
      </article>
      <article class="review-card">
        <p class="team-card__role">You bring</p>
        <h3>Practice &amp; expertise</h3>
        <ul class="checks-list">
          <li>Active Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor credentials</li>
          <li>Professional liability (E&amp;O) insurance</li>
          <li>U.S.-based accounting or bookkeeping practice</li>
          <li>Demonstrable client work experience</li>
          <li>Capacity to take on new engagements responsibly</li>
          <li>Local market knowledge and presence</li>
          <li>Commitment to the platform&rsquo;s quality standard</li>
          <li>Written communication discipline</li>
          <li>Responsiveness within agreed service windows</li>
          <li>Ongoing professional development</li>
        </ul>
      </article>
    </div>
    <p class="in-brief__source stack-8">You keep your existing clients, your existing contracts, and your existing revenue. The network is additive &mdash; TechBrot brings new engagements under the TechBrot brand. Your independent practice continues unchanged.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="partners-benefits">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Operator benefits</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">What the platform actually does for you.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Most independent practices spend more time finding clients than serving them. The platform inverts that.</p>
    </header>
    <ol class="process-diagram">
      <li class="process-step">
        <p class="process-step__number">01 &middot; Demand</p>
        <h3 class="process-step__heading">Qualified engagements, not leads.</h3>
        <p class="process-step__body">By the time an engagement reaches you, TechBrot has already had the discovery call, scoped the work, and confirmed the fit. You receive a qualified engagement with a written scope &mdash; not a cold lead to chase.</p>
        <p class="process-step__body">Engagements are routed by state, industry, capacity, and engagement type. You can decline anything that doesn&rsquo;t fit your practice or your bandwidth without consequence.</p>
      </li>
      <li class="process-step">
        <p class="process-step__number">02 &middot; Brand</p>
        <h3 class="process-step__heading">A national brand behind your local practice.</h3>
        <p class="process-step__body">Clients trust TechBrot before they meet you. The platform&rsquo;s editorial positioning, SEO authority, AI-search presence, and trust signals do the credibility work that takes most independent practices years to build alone.</p>
        <p class="process-step__body">You stay your own firm. The TechBrot association is additive &mdash; it expands what your practice can credibly take on, not what you&rsquo;re forced to be.</p>
      </li>
      <li class="process-step">
        <p class="process-step__number">03 &middot; Infrastructure</p>
        <h3 class="process-step__heading">The operating overhead, handled.</h3>
        <p class="process-step__body">Intake forms, scoping templates, engagement letters, communication infrastructure, document handling, client portal, billing coordination &mdash; the things that fill an operator&rsquo;s week without making them money.</p>
        <p class="process-step__body">An in-house ops team would cost six figures. The platform gives you that leverage as part of the operator relationship.</p>
      </li>
      <li class="process-step">
        <p class="process-step__number">04 &middot; AI &amp; tooling</p>
        <h3 class="process-step__heading">AI-augmented workflow, built in-house.</h3>
        <p class="process-step__body">TechBrot is building operator-facing AI tooling for engagement intake, document handling, categorization assistance, quality-review checklists, and client communication drafting. Tools that compound: more time on real work, less time on operational friction.</p>
        <p class="process-step__body">Operators get early access. The AI augments the operator &mdash; it doesn&rsquo;t replace the judgment that clients pay for.</p>
      </li>
      <li class="process-step">
        <p class="process-step__number">05 &middot; Quality</p>
        <h3 class="process-step__heading">Platform-level review, not self-policing.</h3>
        <p class="process-step__body">Every engagement is reviewed against a defined operating standard. That means consistency for clients and structured feedback for operators &mdash; the kind most independent practices never get.</p>
        <p class="process-step__body">Quality review is a development tool, not a surveillance system. It exists to make operators better, not to second-guess them.</p>
      </li>
      <li class="process-step">
        <p class="process-step__number">06 &middot; Continuity</p>
        <h3 class="process-step__heading">A real institution behind your name.</h3>
        <p class="process-step__body">If life happens &mdash; vacation, illness, capacity changes &mdash; the platform handles continuity without losing client context. Operators get the same protection they extend to clients.</p>
        <p class="process-step__body">You&rsquo;re never the single point of failure. Neither is the client.</p>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="partners-requirements">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Operator requirements</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">What we look for &mdash; and what we don&rsquo;t.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">The standard is the standard. We&rsquo;d rather have the right operators in fewer states than the wrong operators everywhere.</p>
    </header>
    <h3 class="section__heading stack-8">Required</h3>
    <ul class="checks-list">
      <li><strong>Active Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor</strong>Current ProAdvisor status verified through Intuit&rsquo;s public directory. Online Level 2 minimum.</li>
      <li><strong>U.S.-based accounting or bookkeeping practice</strong>A formed business entity (LLC, S-Corp, or PLLC), U.S. tax identification, and an established operating presence.</li>
      <li><strong>Professional liability (E&amp;O) insurance</strong>Active errors &amp; omissions coverage. Minimum coverage limits discussed during application review.</li>
      <li><strong>Demonstrable client work history</strong>At least 2&ndash;3 years of independent practice or equivalent in-firm experience. References available on request.</li>
      <li><strong>Written communication discipline</strong>Client communication that&rsquo;s clear, timely, and professional. Tested during the application review.</li>
    </ul>
    <h3 class="section__heading stack-8">Valued, not required</h3>
    <ul class="checks-list">
      <li><strong>Additional credentials</strong>CPA, EA, CB, AIPB, NACPB credentials are valued. Not a requirement for ProAdvisor-led bookkeeping work.</li>
      <li><strong>Industry specialization</strong>Operators with deep experience in e-commerce, real estate, construction, restaurants, SaaS, or other verticals get prioritized for routing.</li>
      <li><strong>Multi-state experience</strong>Multi-state sales tax, multi-state payroll, and multi-entity engagement experience is valued for complex engagement routing.</li>
      <li><strong>Team capacity</strong>Solo operators and small-team practices are both welcome. Capacity is discussed individually.</li>
    </ul>
    <h3 class="section__heading stack-8">Disqualifying</h3>
    <ul class="checks-list">
      <li><strong>Unresolved licensing or disciplinary issues</strong>Open complaints, board actions, or licensing suspensions disqualify the application.</li>
      <li><strong>Non-U.S. operating presence</strong>Operators must run U.S.-based practices. We&rsquo;re not expanding internationally during the current phase.</li>
      <li><strong>Proprietary-software lock-in</strong>TechBrot operates in the client&rsquo;s existing QuickBooks file. Practices that force clients onto proprietary software aren&rsquo;t a fit.</li>
      <li><strong>No active ProAdvisor certification</strong>Lapsed or never-earned ProAdvisor status disqualifies the application. Renew first, then apply.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="partners-process">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Application process</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">From application to first engagement.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Four phases. Typical timeline three to six weeks. Application is free; no obligation at any stage.</p>
    </header>
    {#- ROUND 11 within-page variety (founder rule 2026-06-13): the
        application process is the page's SECOND sequential component, so
        it takes the design-system .flow treatment (a connected journey
        strip) instead of repeating the numbered .process-diagram used by
        #partners-benefits. The phase journey + timings ride the flow; the
        per-phase detail keeps its baseline H3 headings in review-cards
        (content + equity preserved). All classes are in-bundle/manifest. -#}
    <div class="flow" role="img" aria-label="Application journey: apply in about twenty minutes, a fit call within one to two weeks, verification, then onboarding to the first engagement &mdash; typically three to six weeks total.">
      <div class="flow__step flow__step--accent"><span class="flow__label">1 &middot; Apply</span><span class="flow__sub">~20 min &middot; free</span></div>
      <span class="flow__arrow" aria-hidden="true"><svg width="22" height="10" viewBox="0 0 22 10"><line x1="0" y1="5" x2="16" y2="5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"></line><path d="M14 1 L20 5 L14 9" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"></path></svg></span>
      <div class="flow__step"><span class="flow__label">2 &middot; Fit Call</span><span class="flow__sub">within 1&ndash;2 weeks</span></div>
      <span class="flow__arrow" aria-hidden="true"><svg width="22" height="10" viewBox="0 0 22 10"><line x1="0" y1="5" x2="16" y2="5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"></line><path d="M14 1 L20 5 L14 9" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"></path></svg></span>
      <div class="flow__step"><span class="flow__label">3 &middot; Verification</span><span class="flow__sub">1&ndash;2 weeks</span></div>
      <span class="flow__arrow" aria-hidden="true"><svg width="22" height="10" viewBox="0 0 22 10"><line x1="0" y1="5" x2="16" y2="5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"></line><path d="M14 1 L20 5 L14 9" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"></path></svg></span>
      <div class="flow__step"><span class="flow__label">4 &middot; Onboarding</span><span class="flow__sub">1&ndash;2 weeks</span></div>
    </div>
    <div class="grid-2 stack-8">
      <article class="review-card">
        <h3>Apply</h3>
        <p class="review-card__fact">Submit the application with credentials, practice details, capacity, geographic coverage, and any specializations. Takes about 20 minutes &mdash; <strong>free, no obligation</strong>.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="review-card">
        <h3>Fit Call</h3>
        <p class="review-card__fact">30-minute call to discuss the model, mutual expectations, and what your practice is looking for. Both sides decide whether to continue &mdash; <strong>typically within 1&ndash;2 weeks</strong>.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="review-card">
        <h3>Verification</h3>
        <p class="review-card__fact">Credential verification, insurance review, reference checks, and a brief work-sample discussion. Standard for every operator &mdash; <strong>typically 1&ndash;2 weeks</strong>.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="review-card">
        <h3>Onboarding</h3>
        <p class="review-card__fact">Operator agreement signed. Onboarding to TechBrot&rsquo;s tooling, quality standards, intake workflow, and engagement routing. First engagement scoped within weeks &mdash; <strong>typically 1&ndash;2 weeks</strong>.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
    <div class="hero__actions stack-8">
      <a class="btn btn--primary btn--lg" href="/contact/?intent=partner-apply">Start the Application</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="partners-principles">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Operating principles</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">How the platform treats operators.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">The same principles that govern client engagements govern operator relationships. Same standard, both directions.</p>
    </header>
    {#- ROUND 11 follow-up (founder ruling 2026-06-13): operating principles
        are a PARALLEL list of six, not a sequence, so they take a grid-3
        card layout (not the numbered .process-diagram). This removes the
        last numbered-grid repeat on the page — benefits keeps the numbered
        .process-diagram, process took the .flow, principles is now cards.
        Baseline H3 headings preserved in the cards (content + equity). -#}
    <div class="grid-3">
      <article class="review-card">
        <h3>Independence is preserved.</h3>
        <p class="review-card__fact">Operators are independent businesses, not employees and not franchisees. No territory restrictions, no required signage, no operational lock-in. The relationship is contractual and structured to be fair.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="review-card">
        <h3>Economics are transparent.</h3>
        <p class="review-card__fact">Engagement-level economics, platform fee structure, and payment cadence are documented in the operator agreement. No hidden fees, no surprise charges, no clawbacks.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="review-card">
        <h3>Capacity is respected.</h3>
        <p class="review-card__fact">Operators set their own capacity and can decline engagements that don&rsquo;t fit. The platform routes work to operators who can responsibly take it &mdash; not the other way around.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="review-card">
        <h3>Quality goes both ways.</h3>
        <p class="review-card__fact">Platform-level review applies to TechBrot too. Operators receive structured feedback; operators give structured feedback back. Quality is a system, not a script.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="review-card">
        <h3>Continuity is mutual.</h3>
        <p class="review-card__fact">If an operator leaves the network, the transition is handled professionally &mdash; for clients, for the operator, and for the platform. No hostage situations, no scorched-earth exits.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="review-card">
        <h3>Voice in the platform.</h3>
        <p class="review-card__fact">Active operators inform how TechBrot evolves &mdash; tooling priorities, standards updates, routing logic, AI development. The operators using the platform shape the platform.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="partners-infrastructure">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">The leverage</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">An in-house ops team without the headcount.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="legal-doc__body">
      <p>The reason independent practices stay small isn&rsquo;t talent. It&rsquo;s leverage. A solo operator can serve a finite number of clients well because everything beyond the actual accounting work &mdash; finding clients, scoping engagements, managing communication, handling documents, reviewing for quality, drafting follow-ups &mdash; consumes time that doesn&rsquo;t scale.</p>
      <p>TechBrot is engineered around that constraint. The platform handles intake. The platform scopes the work. The platform reviews for quality. The platform develops AI-assisted tooling that compounds an operator&rsquo;s output without compromising the judgment clients are paying for.</p>
      <p><strong>The operator stays human. The overhead disappears.</strong></p>
      <p>That&rsquo;s what makes the network work. Independent practices keep their independence. They just stop carrying the overhead alone.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="partners-faq">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Operator questions</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading" id="partners-faq-heading">What ProAdvisors ask before applying.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="faq__list">
      {%- for item in faq %}
      <div class="faq__item">
        <h3 class="faq__question"><button class="faq__trigger" type="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="partners-faq-{{ loop.index }}" id="partners-faq-q-{{ loop.index }}">{{ item.q | safe }}</button></h3>
        <div class="faq__answer" id="partners-faq-{{ loop.index }}" data-open="false" role="region" aria-labelledby="partners-faq-q-{{ loop.index }}">
          <p>{{ item.a | safe }}</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
    <p class="faq__more"><a href="#partners-requirements">See full requirements detail &rarr;</a></p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="partners-application-cta">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Apply to the operator network</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">If the model fits, we&rsquo;d like to talk.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Applications are reviewed weekly. We&rsquo;re onboarding in priority states first; if you&rsquo;re outside our current focus areas, we&rsquo;ll let you know honestly and keep your application on file.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="hero__actions">
      <a class="btn btn--primary btn--lg" href="/contact/?intent=partner-apply">Start the Application</a>
    </div>
    <p class="in-brief__source stack-8">Free to apply &middot; 20-minute form &middot; No obligation</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="partners-deeper">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Deeper</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">More about how the network operates.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-2">
      <article class="review-card">
        <h3>Operator benefits</h3>
        <p class="review-card__fact">Detailed breakdown of what the platform delivers &mdash; demand, brand, infrastructure, AI tooling, quality systems, continuity.</p>
        <a class="review-card__link" href="#partners-benefits">Read benefits detail &rarr;</a>
      </article>
      <article class="review-card">
        <h3>Operator requirements</h3>
        <p class="review-card__fact">Full credential, insurance, and experience requirements with specific thresholds, verification process, and disqualifying conditions.</p>
        <a class="review-card__link" href="#partners-requirements">Read requirements detail &rarr;</a>
      </article>
      <article class="review-card">
        <h3>How the network works</h3>
        <p class="review-card__fact">The structural details &mdash; operator vetting, engagement scoping, quality review process, continuity mechanics.</p>
        <a class="review-card__link" href="/about/network/">Read about the network &rarr;</a>
      </article>
      <article class="review-card">
        <h3>Operating methodology</h3>
        <p class="review-card__fact">The four-phase engagement methodology applied across every project. Same standard, every operator, every engagement.</p>
        <a class="review-card__link" href="/about/methodology/">Read the methodology &rarr;</a>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
